Design Tool
1.	Write necessary includes and defines for the application.

2.	Start main.

3.	Define variables for the program.

4.	Display the request to get the first name of the user.

5.	Get the input from the user.

6.	Display the request for the amount of times they want to repeat their first name.

7.	Get the input from the user.

8.	Start the for loop to repeat the line number and the user’s name.

9.	Display the line numbers and the user’s first name however many times the user wanted it to repeat.

10.	End for loop

11.	System pause

12.	End main
